This paper deals with evaluating the Quality of Service (QoS) performance of cellular networks for vehicle-to-everything (V2X) communication, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication technologies (cs.NI). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to predict QoS levels, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses security-related issues, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with the performance of LTE networks, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
